com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.method
Interface NativeInstanceFieldCallback

All Superinterfaces:
NativeBehavior, NativeCallback, NativeCapable, NativeFieldCallback, NativeFieldMethod, NativeInstanceFieldMethod
All Known Subinterfaces:
NativeDirectInstanceFieldCallback, NativeInstanceFieldMethodReflection
public interface NativeInstanceFieldCallback
extends NativeFieldCallback, NativeInstanceFieldMethod

The NativeInstanceFieldCallback is the interface implemented by native capable classes that make accessible Java instance fields from native seen as methods. Java fields are accessed using Java reflection or normal access.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria

Method Detail

onCall

java.lang.Object onCall(java.lang.Object obj,
                        int opcode,
                        java.lang.Object value)
Method called after marshalling to Java the native call.

Parameters:
obj - the native capable object containing the field.
opcode - the operation code used.
value - the new value used to update the field.
Returns:
the current value of the field when reading or any value if writing.
See Also:
NativeInstanceFieldMethod.call(Object,int,Object), NativeConstructorCallback.onCall(Object[])
